Docker Commands
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io
systemctl status docker
sudo docker pull ubuntu
sudo docker images
sudo docker run -itd -p 80:80 --name=assign1 ubuntu
i = interactive, t = terminal, d= detachmode, -p= port first 80 local machine port, 2nd 80 Container, --name=name of the container ubuntu

You can see the container now
sudo docker ps

Enter into the container
sudo docker exec -it assign1 bash (assign1 is the name of the container, you can also provide container id)

